summarize stats output (compute quantiles)

Source: R/tidyMS_stats.R
summarize_cv_quantiles.Rd

summarize stats output (compute quantiles)

summarize_cv_quantiles(
  stats_res,
  config,
  stats = c("sd", "CV"),
  probs = c(0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 0.9)
)

Arguments

stats_res

result of running `summarize_cv`
config

AnalysisConfiguration
stats

summarize either sd or CV
probs

for which quantiles 10, 20 etc.

Examples

library(ggplot2)
library(LFQService)
bb1 <- LFQService::ionstar$filtered()

#> Column added : nr_peptide_Id_IN_protein_Id
config <- bb1$config$clone( deep = TRUE)
data <- bb1$data
stats_res <- summarize_cv(data, config)
summarize_cv_quantiles(stats_res, config)
